# Project Brain — Guidelines

This vault is a **personal knowledge management system** for project documentation. These guidelines ensure consistency and enable effective AI assistance.

## Quick Reference

| Aspect | Standard |
|--------|----------|
| **Frontmatter** | Required on all notes |
| **Tags** | `type/`, `project/`, `stage/` |
| **Back Matter** | Required on all notes |
| **Links** | WikiLinks with `[[Note]]` |
| **Dates** | ISO format `YYYY-MM-DD` |
| **Git** | Conventional Commits |
| **Branches** | `docs/`, `template/`, `fix/` |

## Core Principles

1. **Connection over collection** — Notes link to sources, references, and downstream uses
2. **Atomic and purposeful** — Each note has one clear purpose
3. **Validate before building** — Document hypotheses and experiment results
4. **Decisions as first-class** — ADRs and pivots are documented

